  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\(symmetric)::set.theoretic.relation:on{X}]\nRefines: R\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nsatisfies:\n. forAll: a, b is \\set\n  where:\n  . a \"in\" X\n  . b \"in\" X\n  then:\n  . if:\n    . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{a}:and{b} \"in\" R\n    then:\n    . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{b}:and{a} \"in\" R\nDocumented:\n. adjective: \"symmetric\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{symmetric}\"\n. description: \"A relation $R$ on $X$ is symmetric when $a \\mathbin{R} b$ implies $b \\mathbin{R} a$ for all $a, b \\in X$.\"\nId: \"0fe6a499-901e-4936-8009-00d0c3581f6f\"",
